  "comment": "papi-owned markl-id conformance vectors. Per ADR-0006, papi registers its OWN purposes (papi-doc-sig-v1 = RFC-0001 §10 document signature; papi-proof-sig-v1 = §9.3 proof-claim signature; papi-enroll-att-v1 = FDR-0001 enrollment-receipt attestation; papi-auth-sig-v1 = §5.2 sign-challenge auth signature) and owns these vectors; piggy's go/markl provides only the framework + the ecdsa_p256_sig format. The blech32 body is the framework encoding (binds to the format, not the purpose), so all four purposes share one body for one payload — see TestPapiOwnedVectors, which cross-checks it against the vendored RFC-0002 framework vector. The cross-domain fixture-assembly format is being settled in amarbel-llc/piggy#187.",
